text":"20% cronifica","guid":"JAs9PHkn-Dyh-IRRY9gr5w","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento","guid":"N3ho-9Ue8EbMD47r3tjY3g","children":[{"id":"150","parent":"149","text":"Recuento plaquetas estable\\NObservacion","guid":"NbOxe41qWk33vN2IHFxrEA","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"Hemograma","guid":"siPRDeXkqHRn-M4jGHRP-w","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"C/2 sem el primer mes","guid":"-0r48seCh_HLNSS8uz-dAg","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"C/mes por 6 meses","guid":"vUVuaweaGare_fVtqJjaag","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"151","text":"C/3-6 meses","guid":"bT8UO6Uw5u_WvSeBqZbPrw","children":[]}]},{"id":"155","parent":"150","text":"Educación reconsulta","guid":"7bypHH8Dd_gRvntK14LceA","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"Signos hemorragia","guid":"fcGww4UH-I_DNRmQ1lLOSA","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Prevención hemorragia\\NProcedimiento invasor","guid":"LVu8ywcjepcQw5MUbCp4sw","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"Cirugia","guid":"h9IVOScZxz3ioc4UdxwDhQ","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"Exodoncia","guid":"g4JpZ4fWfoOJvaRXEr7jgQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"155","text":"Gestacion","guid":"XuSbx3OC9GptNbvxIP-usg","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"150","text":"Observación aparición otra\\Nenfermedad autoinmune","guid":"ykxUVcYOghm4Vk4r4YAFBQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"149","text":"Paciente con tratamiento activo","guid":"7DWK0zcef_d17ffjUdjDHQ","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"Hemograma a demanda","guid":"RNsVUbWL8TR5QVwtsHaPYA","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"162","text":"Controles de potencial toxicidad","guid":"q7Syj4vu0RqOsScmcZHtlA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"0","text":"Perlas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"- ¿Cuáles son los mecanismos fisiopatológicos\\Nprincipales del PTI?","guid":"vpv0Dj5Ry7K3rMOqhlSXWg","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Destrucción plaquetaria mediada por autoanticuerpos y\\Nalteración en la producción de plaquetas por megacariocitos.","guid":"3_tigyma5gp_uXmisEHH-g","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"- ¿Qué exámenes son imprescindibles en la evaluación\\Ninicial de un paciente con sospecha de PTI?","guid":"e5DW6TsXa8kIIAym_eKD6w","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"Hemograma completo, frotis sanguíneo,\\Npruebas de VIH y hepatitis C.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"165","text":"- ¿Cuál es la principal indicación de\\Ntratamiento en PTI?","guid":"qWqhfdoECTDZo-yM1ZkoYQ","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Presencia de sangrado o recuento\\Nplaquetario <20.000/uL.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"165","text":"- ¿Cuáles son las opciones de primera línea\\Nen el tratamiento del PTI?","guid":"JHigX621rWr9mWwdnPNcBQ","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"Corticoides (prednisona, dexametasona)\\Ne inmunoglobulina intravenosa (IgIV).","guid":"Y1N0a2IF-ATVJOLxG2Sxcw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"0","text":"Definición:","guid":"6BEGTuBNl25gZZe9Ub4c9w","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"- El PTI es un trastorno autoinmune adquirido caracterizado por trombocitopenia\\Naislada (plaquetas <100. 000/uL) sin una causa identificable (1).","guid":"qN8OBS2h7aAxx7HmCRpbhw","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"- Previamente conocida como púrpura trombocitopénica idiopática, el término PTI\\Nrefuerza su naturaleza inmune y la ausencia de púrpura en muchos casos (2).","guid":"GmFLWigf2xxnjM6KXz_SIA","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"- Destrucción plaquetaria mediada por autoanticuerpos, principalmente IgG, dirigidos contra glicoproteínas (GP) de superficie como GPIIb/IIIa y GPIb/IX (3).","guid":"8ViZu4oN7Pba5gnf8QxmGg","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"- Producción plaquetaria alterada por efecto directo de autoanticuerpos y células T autorreactivas sobre megacariocitos (4).","guid":"h8mKlKvaCQPX8IZLzmz1dA","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"177","text":"- Objetivos terapéuticos: Suprimir producción de autoanticuerpos, modular respuesta de células T, estimular trombopoyesis.","guid":"fJIqC29tq5gp3uQ3YcmPiw","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"177","text":"- Futura investigación: Rol de células T regulatorias, polimorfismos genéticos, nuevas terapias dirigidas.","guid":"lvui7NA8EU6g1lnm0GRzRg","children":[]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"- Incidencia anual: 1-6 casos por 100.000 adultos.\\NPrevalencia 8-12 por 100.000. Aumenta con la edad (5).","guid":"DGIY-1NJE9t02fmUvB_j9w","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"182","text":"- En Chile, no hay datos epidemiológicos robustos publicados.","guid":"cOkVcgHNmpI2-PfcHqOcww","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"182","text":"- Morbilidad asociada a sangrados mucocutáneos y\\Nfatiga. Discapacidad por limitación de actividades.","guid":"3pH1GO_BQT_4gijCAcU3Pw","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"182","text":"- Mortalidad <1% por sangrados\\Ngraves (intracraneal) (6).","guid":"l0NmOfvPxQCam2B24x-6Ng","children":[]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"0","text":"Factores de riesgo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"- Edad avanzada, especialmente >60 años (RR 2.3) (7).","guid":"52kgS8ipz6Ig9qNAs3lyBg","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"- Sexo femenino en edad reproductiva (RR 1.2-1.7).","guid":"ylNVrAPDyxghNvF3jVhplg","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"187","text":"- Enfermedades autoinmunes (LES, SAF, tiroiditis) (RR 2-3).","guid":"Ebt72m9ZOIeER1szWY_K4Q","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"187","text":"- Infecciones virales recientes (VEB, CMV, VHC, VIH).","guid":"G_wneDmXdy7IuDIEtaIhEg","children":[]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"0","text":"Causas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"- PTI primario (80%): Sin condición subyacente identificada.","guid":"hxpKmAsEP_7qDXck1jztmw","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"192","text":"- PTI secundario (20%): Asociado a enfermedades autoinmunes (LES, SAF),\\Ninmunodeficiencias (IDCV, VIH), infecciones (H. pylori, VHC), neoplasias linfoides, fármacos (8).","guid":"L1iNzpXkag1RafMEmjLxtg","children":[]}]},{"id":"195","parent":"0","text":"Clínica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"- Curso insidioso. Asintomático en 20-30%, hallazgo incidental.","guid":"jxjfuxxE4LcJaIBPygvBQQ","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"- Sangrado mucocutáneo (>60%): petequias, equimosis, epistaxis, gingivorragia, menorragia.\\N\"Púrpura húmeda\" en mucosas es signo de alarma.","guid":"G9ho-lPE3ykw0cSrPmCtxw","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"195","text":"- Fatiga (hasta 40%) y calidad de vida disminuida.","guid":"WufyhVPra4bAbsn-HwNe0Q","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"195","text":"- Signos de alarma: cefalea intensa, visión borrosa (sospecha hemorragia intracraneal), melena (hemorragia digestiva).","guid":"DdhtuRRVXUrs8X2HtKLeJw","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"195","text":"- Factores de mal pronóstico: Edad >60 años (OR 2.5), sangrado previo (OR 27), plaquetas <10.000/uL.","guid":"gwq4qcOvSfjf4InErMf9rg","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"195","text":"- Complicaciones: Hemorragia intracraneal (1-2%), hemorragia digestiva (9-10%).\\NSospechar si cefalea, alteración de conciencia, hematemesis/melena (9).","guid":"fztba2jIG1-3GUOfvDLaaQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"202","parent":"0","text":"Estudio:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"- Hemograma completo: Trombocitopenia aislada, VCM y hemoglobina normales (10).","guid":"iXoywIW8-AE4E5XdNYZ-1A","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"- Frotis sanguíneo: Descartar seudotrombocitopenia, trombocitopenia hereditaria (plaquetas anormales). Sensibilidad 80%.","guid":"BlZYfOq3vCYbixEYgMINWw","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"- Pruebas hepáticas, función renal y perfil de coagulación generalmente normales.","guid":"m6JejhZefF00-nqGgvY8Aw","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"202","text":"- Serología VIH (OR 3) y VHC (OR 10): Descartar PTI secundaria.","guid":"EPc1mLKP-jsMYQC3BeQ6lw","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"202","text":"- Médula ósea: No indicada rutinariamente. Considerar si citopenias adicionales, displasia, falla a tratamiento (Especificidad 75%).","guid":"nX6BRxVfR1OJHzZyTI0Ujg","children":[]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"- Clínico: Trombocitopenia aislada (<100.000/uL) sin causa evidente, megacariocitos normales/aumentados en médula ósea.","guid":"5J4yX761V5PyLdmEmuw3cw","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"208","text":"- Criterios PTI primario: Ausencia de condición subyacente (enf. autoinmune, malignidad, infección).","guid":"oHyc1C0hZn9weElnCapBtQ","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"208","text":"- Criterios PTI secundario: Trombocitopenia + condición asociada (LES, VIH, etc).","guid":"VyauLZXPH5UdZ6MFJC76Qw","children":[]},{"id":"212","parent":"208","text":"- No hay Gold Standard. Es diagnóstico de exclusión (11).","guid":"lzB2eTC55clgWeWQfSJQJw","children":[]}]},{"id":"213","parent":"0","text":"Diagnósticos\\Ndiferenciales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"- Síndrome purpúrico: Vasculitis, PTT, sepsis.","guid":"FIJYvWlYa5nApm85wkHowQ","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"213","text":"- Trombocitopenia: Seudotrombocitopenia, incidental (gestacional), PTI secundaria, Sd. antifosfolípidos,\\Ntrombocitopenia inducida por fármacos, trombocitopenia hereditaria, aplasia medular (12).","guid":"7TJKaDR5XQQC2UjHYncu7w","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento (13):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"- Objetivo: Mantener recuento plaquetario seguro (>20.000-30.000/uL), evitar sangrados. No normalizar plaquetas.","guid":"9RvxtYhSunshfQkE_oP-Cg","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"- No farmacológico: Evitar deportes de contacto, AINEs. Cuidado bucal. Dieta rica en hierro/folato si hay sangrado.","guid":"czOG3DBBt_XPO9e_DJJiRw","children":[]},{"id":"219","parent":"216","text":"- Farmacológico:","guid":"5OjGIdeGiqx0zFVKkXFp_w","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"- Primera línea:","guid":"7NcI7xGfoyd2dnRYVxcKgA","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"- Prednisona 1 mg/kg/d x 1-2 semanas, luego reducir 10 mg/sem hasta suspender.","guid":"_y5ucbA8yyFccSs-pILPag","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"220","text":"- Dexametasona 40 mg/d x 4 días cada 2-4 semanas máx. 3 ciclos.","guid":"Ia-k4tweOG2Z6lGbuf9FoA","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"220","text":"- IgIV 1 g/kg/d x 1-2 días. Reservar para sangrado grave o procedimientos urgentes.","guid":"4uVpsmIZcjJpGFJ6zXAl6g","children":[]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"219","text":"- Segunda línea\\N(refractarios, recaída):","guid":"XC-jBoGG4XVGPbRaM5_Ddw","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"- Agonistas receptor trombopoyetina: Eltrombopag 50 mg/d, Romiplostim 1-10 mcg/kg/sem SC.","guid":"bKPXh6kkANxahg9TfRyfSA","children":[]},{"id":"226","parent":"224","text":"- Rituximab 375 mg/m2/sem x 4 dosis.","guid":"1bsvH5R5zM4-jcRjJyEpEQ","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"224","text":"- Esplenectomía si falla tratamiento médico >12 meses.","guid":"VRfZKXWyhhKhJX_8F8sFMg","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"224","text":"- Otros: Azatioprina, danazol, micofenolato, fostamatinib, combinaciones.","guid":"-VjOpN4c4xKuwPAiMODE8A","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"224","text":"- Advertencias: Riesgo infecciones (corticoides, IgIV, rituximab), trombosis (agonistas TPO), sepsis post-esplenectomía.","guid":"Sag6NwKL4I-Tv9bH9FH2wg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"0","text":"Seguimiento y\\Npronóstico:","guid":"1ahm8NjXz1z78Ijs04C74g","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"- Plaquetas c/1-2 sem hasta >30. 000/uL, luego espaciar según respuesta. Hemograma c/1-3 meses.","guid":"JI8kDHD_Ud1j5Q38bLojZg","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"- Si corticoide >4 sem: Presión, glicemia, densitometría, profilaxis TBC.","guid":"0kpSF9aVkLkzGwL1QA0Vrg","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"- Equipo multidisciplinario: Hematólogo, médico general, enfermería, psicólogo, dentista.","guid":"tvT-BF7KVLXf9LiJ4dfcCA","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"- Remisión espontánea 10-20% a 6 meses. Recaída hasta 80%. Mortalidad 1-5% por hemorragia, terapia inmunosupresora (14).","guid":"lfEVIXCajOEvRZUpLnBeIg","children":[]}]},{"id":"235","parent":"0","text":"Prevención:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"- Identificar y tratar causa de PTI secundario (erradicación H. pylori, terapia antirretroviral si VIH, etc).","guid":"GgVxG3CUY5hlBl-hN50amA","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"- Vacunación antineumocócica pre-esplenectomía (15).","guid":"DjunfwVBKj_Dsw3BJus_oA","children":[]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"0","text":"Tamizaje:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"- Hemograma es examen de elección. Criterios: Plaquetas aisladas <100.000/uL.\\NSensibilidad 95%, especificidad 60%.","guid":"RkW6gCD-3hwAWjkt8eSBYQ","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"- No se recomienda tamizaje rutinario en población general asintomática (16).","guid":"B_lWZ-WO11yyYMk14XVEmg","children":[]}]},{"id":"241","parent":"0","text":"Aspectos Geriátricos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"242","parent":"241","text":"- Mayor incidencia en >60 años. Alta sospecha en trombocitopenia \"no esperada\".","guid":"3mWaExy5Mo1meD_E1ucc1A","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"241","text":"- Mayor riesgo de sangrados por comorbilidades (HTA, anticoagulación) y fragilidad capilar.","guid":"Hh1ROE_KLh686nhYEyKcZQ","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"241","text":"- Corticoides con más efectos adversos (osteoporosis, delirio). Preferir dexametasona.","guid":"MBcXykNybCwF1UpRNvbhtg","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"241","text":"- IgIV segura pero mayor riesgo eventos trombóticos. Monitorizar.","guid":"9e5ElUOiCyF_wRLJ3uO3OA","children":[]},{"id":"246","parent":"241","text":"- TPO-RAs pocos efectos adversos, buena opción (17).","guid":"vtl1DKAPlP3naGz4lMnepw","children":[]}]},{"id":"247","parent":"0","text":"Referencias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"248","parent":"247","text":"1. Rodeghiero F, et al. Blood. 2009;113(11):2386-93.","guid":"bGQE0Et-5VfxX0MkYVqKfg","children":[]},{"id":"249","parent":"247","text":"2. Cooper N, et al. Br J Haematol. 2006;133(5):451-8.","guid":"N8qAhgCthrn-cuOCs1ps7g","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"247","text":"3. Cines DB, et al. Blood. 2009;113(26):6511-21.","guid":"zfmgPA3uIi6bCPa6JuKdxA","children":[]},{"id":"251","parent":"247","text":"4. Zufferey A, et al. Front Immunol. 2021;12:650129.","guid":"BqOLUsKLfxTwDSfx0QV4fw","children":[]},{"id":"252","parent":"247","text":"5. Moulis G, et al. Blood. 2014;124(22):3308-15.","guid":"L-efWTb9ZGQWWHi-cogNxw","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"247","text":"6. Cohen YC, et al. Arch Intern Med. 2000;160(11):1630-8.","guid":"JOM-d-R4JwOC52_oXBGzjg","children":[]},{"id":"254","parent":"247","text":"7. Cortelazzo S, et al. Blood. 1991;77(1):31-5.","guid":"OQSlzZFwSzdnsh3ud0G6NA","children":[]},{"id":"255","parent":"247","text":"8. Cines DB, et al. Semin Hematol. 2009;46(1 Suppl 2):S2-14.","guid":"l8oZ2fLWQeRCYNk-4OcB1A","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"247","text":"9. Neunert C, et al. J Thromb Haemost. 2015;13(3):457-64.","guid":"H0dxVsu8bA2Q1CZlVZywbw","children":[]},{"id":"257","parent":"247","text":"10. Provan D, et al. Blood. 2010;115(2):168-86.","guid":"5K4501jHRGQllVMyh6ofNQ","children":[]},{"id":"258","parent":"247","text":"11. Neunert C, et al. Blood Adv. 2019;3(23):3829-3866.","guid":"CzGJhVw_F12Xs6qz-qiopA","children":[]},{"id":"259","parent":"247","text":"12. Onisâi M, et al. Rom J Intern Med. 2021;59(2):132-140.","guid":"qP9Dnm3PdS_w9ThFYBX-Bw","children":[]},{"id":"260","parent":"247","text":"13. Provan D, et al. Blood Adv. 2019;3(22):3780-3817.","guid":"RWxcy2VttOgQxVZwX2ux1Q","children":[]},{"id":"261","parent":"247","text":"14. Vianelli N, et al. Haematologica. 2001; 86(5):504-9.","guid":"tlFbHUY-I-ifsqe5DDYEDg","children":[]},{"id":"262","parent":"247","text":"15. Rubin LG, et al. Ann Intern Med. 2014;161(7):474-81.","guid":"UzvT0d8ksnzCChBYn7l-pw","children":[]},{"id":"263","parent":"247","text":"16. Chee YL, et al. Br J Haematol. 2008;140(5):496-504.","guid":"NkGwAzN7v6c8yu5dNLw78Q","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"247","text":"17. Gonzalez-Lopez TJ, et al. Haematologica. 2015;100(8):1005-11.","guid":"qR-9hioX6LbkQvYxyaEZ1Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"265","parent":"0","text":"Abreviaturas:","guid":"GH7D4aB6HtpN6Juw1U_0Nw","children":[{"id":"266","parent":"265","text":"- VEB: Virus Epstein-Barr","guid":"n6x9GC4FwR_0aTyozva2Ow","children":[]},{"id":"267","parent":"265","text":"- CMV: Citomegalovirus","guid":"-sTPjYxhA_WfBOpFpw0M3g","children":[]},{"id":"268","parent":"265","text":"- IDCV: Inmunodeficiencia común variable","guid":"8oojuH8XoekhEVWDV1ZiFQ","children":[]},{"id":"269","parent":"265","text":"- PTT: Purpura trombótica trombocitopénica","guid":"OzoKECs7LvKUtiWIjY4Lrw","children":[]},{"id":"270","parent":"265","text":"- IgIV: Inmunoglobulina intravenosa","guid":"j4UywyDeU68TftwLv9nfDw","children":[]},{"id":"271","parent":"265","text":"- TPO-RAs: Agonistas del receptor de trombopoyetina","guid":"PaK_43pnXAp2ZKe_eCI8mQ","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":271,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Hematología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Purpura Trombocitopenica Inmune-2024-1","id":"map_845","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Purpura Trombocitopenica Inmune-2024-1"}